item.title: Productivity
item.description: Productivity So you probably have a couple thousand and a half things to do and 99% of them should have been done by now, but you didn’t get enough time and that’s why you will start tomorrow fresh again on achieving these, where tomorrow is some mystical land where 99% of the human productivity lives. Do you see a common pattern over the years where you wanted to do a lot of things but weren’t able to?
